             ;
             ;					    Whirlwind
             ;					Simulator by G.Fedorkow
             ;		  github.com/gfedorkow/Whirlwind-Instruction-Simulator
             ;
             ;        *** TNMoC's Count to 1,000,000 benchmark ***
             ;
             ; L. Stabile
             ; June 28, 2026
             ;
             ;           Unrolled inner loop
             ;
             ; Use the factoring 2000 * 500 = 1000000. Unroll the inner
             ; loop to 2000 sp instructions. This is the most we can
             ; fit in a single 2048-word memory bank wrt the possible
             ; factors.

             ; Since with the loop unrolled it doesn't have to do
             ; anything, I used the shortest-time nop in whirlwind, an
             ; sp (jump), at 15 usec. So we just jump from one
             ; instruction to the next.
             ;
             ; Clocks at 15 sec (15,022,030 usec), 1001000 instruction cycles.

       loop:
     label0: sp label1
     label1: sp label2
     label2: sp label3
     label3: sp label4
     label4: sp label5
     label5: sp label6
     label6: sp label7
     label7: sp label8
     label8: sp label9
     label9: sp label10
